{
  "info": {
    "name": "Student Path — Auth, User & Bus APIs",
    "description": "## OTP login policy\n\n- OTP is **login-only**.\n- Phone must already exist in `users.phone` (existing account).\n- **No registration flow** is performed by `send-otp` or `verify-otp`.\n- If phone is not registered, auth endpoints return validation error (422).\n\n## Tokens & scoping (matches web dashboard)\n\n| Variable | When to use |\n|----------|-------------|\n| `token` | After **verify-otp**, the test script stores the Sanctum token here. Use for **read** requests: `GET` list/show on schools, students, guardians, drivers, and trips. Non-admins are **school-scoped** (via `users.school_id` or linked `driver.school_id`). Also use for **user profile**, **language**, and **`/api/bus/my-bus`** (driver’s own bus — not the same as admin bus CRUD). |\n| `admin_token` | **Required** for any **write** to schools/students/guardians/drivers/trips: `POST`, `PUT`, `DELETE` on `/api/schools…`, `/api/students…`, `/api/guardians…`, `/api/drivers…`, `/api/trips…`. Token must be for a user with `is_admin: true` (seed admin, tinker, or personal access token). If you use `token` for these, you will get **403** `forbidden` for non-admins. |\n| `school_id`, `driver_id`, `student_id`, `guardian_id`, `trip_id` | Set from a `GET` list response; used in paths and bodies. |\n\n## 403 (admin-only writes)\n\nNon-admins who call a mutation on schools/students/guardians/drivers/trips receive **403**:\n\n```json\n{ \"success\": false, \"data\": {}, \"msg\": \"forbidden\" }\n```\n\nSome **GET** cases (e.g. resource from another school) return the same. If the account has no school scope, you may see:\n\n`\"A school must be linked to this account to perform this action.\"` (on scoped reads when scope is missing).\n",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    {
      "key": "base_url",
      "value": "http://localhost:8000"
    },
    {
      "key": "token",
      "value": ""
    },
    {
      "key": "admin_token",
      "value": ""
    },
    {
      "key": "school_id",
      "value": "1"
    },
    {
      "key": "driver_id",
      "value": "1"
    },
    {
      "key": "student_id",
      "value": "1"
    },
    {
      "key": "guardian_id",
      "value": "1"
    },
    {
      "key": "trip_id",
      "value": "1"
    }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "Auth",
      "description": "OTP works only for **existing users** (login flow only). `POST /api/auth/send-otp` and `POST /api/auth/verify-otp` do **not** register new users. If the phone is not found in `users`, the API returns 422 validation error. On **200** from `verify-otp`, the test script stores `data.token` into `token`.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "POST /api/auth/send-otp",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Accept",
                "value": "application/json"
              },
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"phone\": \"7701234567\"\n}"
            },
            "url": "{{base_url}}/api/auth/send-otp"
          },
          "description": "Login OTP request for an **already registered** phone number only. No auto-registration. Unregistered phone returns 422."
        },
        {
          "name": "POST /api/auth/verify-otp",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
                  "  try {",
                  "    const j = pm.response.json();",
                  "    const t = j.data && (j.data.token || j.data.access_token);",
                  "    if (t) {",
                  "      pm.collectionVariables.set('token', t);",
                  "    }",
                  "  } catch (e) { /* ignore */ }",
                  "}"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Accept",
                "value": "application/json"
              },
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"phone\": \"7701234567\",\n  \"code\": \"1234\"\n}"
            },
            "url": "{{base_url}}/api/auth/verify-otp"
          },
          "description": "Verifies OTP for an **existing user** only and returns a login token. Does not create user/driver/student/guardian/school records."
        },
        {
          "name": "GET /api/auth/me",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Accept",
                "value": "application/json"
              },
              {
                "key": "Authorization",
                "value": "Bearer {{token}}"
              }
            ],
            "url": "{{base_url}}/api/auth/me"
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "POST /api/auth/logout",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Accept",
                "value": "application/json"
              },
              {
                "key": "Authorization",
                "value": "Bearer {{token}}"
              }
            ],
            "url": "{{base_url}}/api/auth/logout"
          }
        }
      ]
    },
